2B buyers some particular products but in a huge volume, so they are quite selective and do a lot of research before making a final decision. So In B2B business, you have to meet every possible from product discovery to final purchase to increase conversions which is only possible through a comprehensive e-commerce platform like Adobe Commerce.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In other e-commerce platforms, you have to do many 3rd party integrations and custom development, while in Adobe Commerce, you will get pre-built B2B features such as:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Quote Management</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Price Negotiations</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Custom Pricing</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Catalogs</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Multi-channel order management</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Support for orders and workflows</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>3. Hybrid Business Model Support</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/aOxld7Go4Cg\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/aOxld7Go4Cg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Changing the business model as per the new trends or adopting new verticals is not a new trend in the e-commerce industry. For instance, many B2B businesses sell directly to the end consumers for more sales. However, running a hybrid business model requires optimum insights into the targeted customers’ preferences and buying behavior in the online business. Adobe Commerce gives you all these required insights in a user-friendly way. Many features in Adobe Commerce make it perfect for hybrid companies, such as:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Ability to manage multiple products and stores</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Omnichannel or consistent experience for B2B and B2C channels</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Access to unified data for optimizing business strategies</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>4. Self-Service Features</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/KllhoxmQTSc\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/KllhoxmQTSc\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Today’s educated and modern customers prefer self-service, especially in the B2B industry. The B2B industry customers like to do their research before making a final purchase, and Adobe Commerce streamlines the journey before making the final purchasing decision. There are several self-service features in the Adobe Commerce, such as:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Role and permission setting</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Make orders by uploading CSV or by SKU</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Management of leftover credit, purchases, and quotes</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Writing and publishing product reviews</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Reward points tracking, including gift cards and store credits</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Checking order history and analyzing it</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Easy re-ordering of previous orders</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>5. Page Builder</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/XWCfhy2kwGU\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/XWCfhy2kwGU\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Page Builder is one of the USPs of Adobe Commerce. It lets you create, edit and modify the website pages without needing developers. Thus the customer service teams and marketing teams don’t need to be technical expertise to create new pages. The simple drag-and-drop tools allow for agile marketing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>6. Easy Integrations</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/sOVtXt-xx4c\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/sOVtXt-xx4c\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Another significant aspect by which Adobe Commerce is different from other e-commerce CMS is its ability to integrate with 3rd party channels such as CRMs and other customer service tools by APIs or extensions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The building block of Adobe Commerce is Magento which is an open-source platform. Thus, it allows for easy and fast integration of CRMs and tools for optimizing business processes and reducing workload.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>7. Product Recommendations</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/i0oDj4zF56E\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/i0oDj4zF56E\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Like live search, this feature of Adobe Commerce utilizes the users’ data such as previous search history, products viewed, order history, etc. Popular brands such as Amazon are generating 70% of their sales using this feature; thus, it becomes important for retailers to leverage this brand as much as possible.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The recommendation feature works for B2B merchants as well. In this scenario, recommended items are tailored to the product line that a particular customer buys.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>8. Mobile Responsive</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/HQpS7z55UF0\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/HQpS7z55UF0\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Today more than half of the customers browse online stores through mobile devices. Thus, it is important to provide a mobile-first design to the buyers. Adobe Commerce comes with PWA Studio, by which you can develop a mobile app-like website.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A Progressive Web Application (PWA) is an excellent tool for new business owners who can’t afford to have a separate mobile application and web application. It is cheap to develop a Magento PWA than a native mobile application.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>9. Flexibility</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Flexibility is another key aspect of the online business. In today’s customer experience-focused world, you must choose an e-commerce development platform that allows maximum customization. Fortunately, Adobe Commerce gives you the flexibility to customize the UI and overall experience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>10. Scalability</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While going into an online business, you must consider that you may need to scale up your business in the future. Thus, the chosen e-commerce development platform should be scalable for future purposes. It should be scalable, robust, and cost –effect. Adobe Commerce is all of these.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Depending on your business needs and financial status, you can quickly scale up or down the Adobe Commerce store. Also, you will pay based on the revenue you made in the store, which lets you avoid paying for capacity you don’t use.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Wrapping Up</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This article has gone through the ten primary reasons that make Adobe Commerce a perfect fit for your online business needs. It may ostensibly seem expensive if you are on a tight budget, but it would be more economical in the long run than any other e-commerce development platform. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','What Makes Adobe Commerce Perfect For An eCommerce Store?','Adobe Commerce is a highly robust and powerful e-commerce platform. Using the Adobe Commerce platform, you can deliver a seamless customer experience, optimize business processes and increase sales. ','inherit','closed','closed','','39-autosave-v1','','','2023-02-07 22:21:48','2023-02-07 15:21:48','',39,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=43',0,'revision','',0),(44,1,'2023-02-09 22:51:49','2023-02-07 15:24:07',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','44','','','2023-02-09 22:51:49','2023-02-09 15:51:49','',0,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=44',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(45,1,'2023-02-09 22:51:49','2023-02-07 15:24:07',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','45','','','2023-02-09 22:51:49','2023-02-09 15:51:49','',0,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=45',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(46,1,'2023-02-08 21:14:44','2023-02-08 14:14:44','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A good search is a backbone of a good UX in an e-commerce store. And if you have used Magento for a considerable period of time then you must have found it challenging to have a good search on your Magento store without using any 3rd party extension. Historically, Magento has been notorious for its “<strong>not so impressive</strong>” search feature. There was a very simple algorithm in the Magento 1 which didn’t provide such good results most of the time. In Magento 2, things improved and it started using ElasticSearch which was quite better regarding search results relevancy and additional features like synonyms, etc. Still, without making some tweaks and modifications, it isn’t yet the best option.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the 2021 Adobe Summit, a new search service called <strong>Live Search</strong> was introduced for Adobe Commerce. This is an official search solution of Adobe which is focused to bring the searching to a new height by utilizing AI and other advanced technologies. If you are using Adobe Commerce as an e-commerce platform for your store, then you can use this service free of cost by installing the corresponding module from the marketplace Magento Live Search. The amazing thing about this module is that it showcases a new service-based approach that Adobe may use in its future versions. It is an API-first service with easy deployment through JavaScript SDK and Graph QL options. Adobe Commerce gives merchants the flexibility to deliver these astonishing user experiences without powerful tools.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\"><strong><em>Do you know that 43% of the users go directly to the website’s search bar?</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The installation process of this module is quite similar to other modules. You just need to generate an API key from your Magento account. This key will be used for communication with other Adobe Commerce services. After the installation and configuration of the module, you have to wait for some time for the indexing of data. If you have configured everything correctly, you will find the Live Search on the main marketing tab of your Admin Panel.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":48,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/customers-prefer-to-pay-1024x572-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-48\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The notion that the CX has a significant impact on the connection between a brand and its customers has been demonstrated several times via surveys, studies, and statistics. According to an Oracle survey,<strong> 86% </strong>of consumers would pay more for a better CX, whereas <strong>89% </strong>would go to a rival if they had a bad CX.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>How Does Live Search Functionality Work?</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/KllhoxmQTSc\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/KllhoxmQTSc\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For e-commerce retailers, giving the right search results to users without introducing any technical capabilities or delays is a huge competitive advantage – Adobe</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An improvement in the search functionality of your store will not just improve customer experience but can also affect the conversion rates. Better search results can lead to 1.8x more conversions. Search is the first medium by which the user interacts with your online store.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Utilizing Artificial intelligence and Machine Learning technologies, the merchants get “searchandizing” capabilities that can deliver customized search results for more conversion rates and sales. This feature gives fast search results and is more efficient. In a B2B commerce store especially, it will help retailers enhance the search experience with features like “search-as-you-type”.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The merchants also get accurate reports on the basis of users’ queries and thus they can refine their strategies as per the users’ mindsets and improve sales. The product recommendations will also get improved by these queries which again lead to improved CX and sales. Since it has been powered by Machine Learning, the results will also be more accurate and personalized.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>1. <strong>Live Search Tools</strong>: Adobe Commerce</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":49,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Live-Search-Tools-768x429-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-49\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After installing the Live Search, you will find a screen where you can configure facets, synonyms, rules, or perform API requests in a search engine. Let’s discuss each of these in more detail:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>1. Facets</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You must have found several attributes listed in the filters of a page, mainly a product listing page. These attributes are called <strong>facets</strong>. You can add new attributes in the standard way from Admin -> Attributes -> Product. Here you will find the newly added attributes in the Faceting section of the Live Search Configuration. Again, you have to wait for some time to reflect the newly added attributes populated in the search configuration. The configuration of facets is also very simple. You can configure order and type of sorting and can pin some attributes to have them always on the top of the filter panel.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>2. Synonyms</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many instances when the user types synonyms or related words of a product in the search query. For e.g. the users may type “sneakers” instead of shoes in the query. In the Synonyms tab, you can configure what keywords should be considered synonyms for a particular product name. The best thing here is the ability to set either two-way (search for a dog, leads to pedigree and vice versa) or one way (search for a cloth on head, get scarf but not vice versa).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>3. Rules</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rules are the most exciting feature. Here you can configure how the search results will look based on the searched query. For e.g. you can create a rule that pins a particular product if the search query contains “shoe”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many merchants were waiting for this feature. This is the reality of the e-commerce industry. Search is not just a UX tool that helps users to find a particular product but it also has become a strong marketing tool. Having flexibility over what users will see in your store gives an extra chance to promote your products.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The GraphQL tab is helpful for many developers. It allows to create an API request and see the direct output from the search service.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>2. Under The Hood : Adobe Commerce</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The most appealing fact about the new search is that the search functionality doesn’t take place in the platform itself – earlier it used to be. It collects all the required data about the catalog and sends it to the external search service within Adobe’s infrastructure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The configurations are also stored on this external service as well. If a user searches for a particular keyword, a request will be sent by the system to the mentioned external service using GraphQL. Adobe Sensei will process the service and send back the respective result.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://magento.com/products/live-search\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more about Live Search</a></strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://marketplace.magento.com/magento-live-search.html?_ga=2.14039863.1236502679.1624423008-362010396.1599655295\" target=\"_blank\">Download Live Search for Free</a></strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Wrapping Up</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Searching is an integral part of the ecommerce store UX and it plays a major role in increasing the conversion rates. Adobe Commerce comes with an astonishing search functionality free of cost that other ecommerce platforms are not capable of providing even after using 3rd party paid plugins. Hire the best Adobe Commerce development company, which has expertise in developing Adobe Commerce stores from scratch.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Live Search In Adobe Commerce: How It Improves CX?','In the 2021 Adobe Summit, a new search service called Live Search was introduced for Adobe Commerce. This is an official search solution of Adobe which is focused to bring the searching to a new height by utilizing AI and other advanced technologies.','publish','open','open','','live-search-in-adobe-commerce-how-it-improves-cx','','','2023-02-08 21:14:44','2023-02-08 14:14:44','',0,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=46',0,'post','',0),(47,1,'2023-02-08 21:04:58','2023-02-08 14:04:58','','Live-Search-In-Adobe-Commerce-','','inherit','open','closed','','live-search-in-adobe-commerce','','','2023-02-08 21:04:58','2023-02-08 14:04:58','',46,'https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Live-Search-In-Adobe-Commerce-.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(48,1,'2023-02-08 21:05:49','2023-02-08 14:05:49','','customers-prefer-to-pay-1024x572','','inherit','open','closed','','customers-prefer-to-pay-1024x572','','','2023-02-08 21:05:49','2023-02-08 14:05:49','',46,'https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/customers-prefer-to-pay-1024x572-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(49,1,'2023-02-08 21:09:20','2023-02-08 14:09:20','','Live-Search-Tools-768x429','','inherit','open','closed','','live-search-tools-768x429','','','2023-02-08 21:09:20','2023-02-08 14:09:20','',46,'https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Live-Search-Tools-768x429-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(50,1,'2023-02-08 21:14:44','2023-02-08 14:14:44','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A good search is a backbone of a good UX in an e-commerce store. And if you have used Magento for a considerable period of time then you must have found it challenging to have a good search on your Magento store without using any 3rd party extension. Historically, Magento has been notorious for its “<strong>not so impressive</strong>” search feature. There was a very simple algorithm in the Magento 1 which didn’t provide such good results most of the time. In Magento 2, things improved and it started using ElasticSearch which was quite better regarding search results relevancy and additional features like synonyms, etc. Still, without making some tweaks and modifications, it isn’t yet the best option.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the 2021 Adobe Summit, a new search service called <strong>Live Search</strong> was introduced for Adobe Commerce. This is an official search solution of Adobe which is focused to bring the searching to a new height by utilizing AI and other advanced technologies. If you are using Adobe Commerce as an e-commerce platform for your store, then you can use this service free of cost by installing the corresponding module from the marketplace Magento Live Search. The amazing thing about this module is that it showcases a new service-based approach that Adobe may use in its future versions. It is an API-first service with easy deployment through JavaScript SDK and Graph QL options. Adobe Commerce gives merchants the flexibility to deliver these astonishing user experiences without powerful tools.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\"><strong><em>Do you know that 43% of the users go directly to the website’s search bar?</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The installation process of this module is quite similar to other modules. You just need to generate an API key from your Magento account. This key will be used for communication with other Adobe Commerce services. After the installation and configuration of the module, you have to wait for some time for the indexing of data. If you have configured everything correctly, you will find the Live Search on the main marketing tab of your Admin Panel.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":48,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/customers-prefer-to-pay-1024x572-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-48\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The notion that the CX has a significant impact on the connection between a brand and its customers has been demonstrated several times via surveys, studies, and statistics. According to an Oracle survey,<strong> 86% </strong>of consumers would pay more for a better CX, whereas <strong>89% </strong>would go to a rival if they had a bad CX.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>How Does Live Search Functionality Work?</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/KllhoxmQTSc\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/KllhoxmQTSc\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For e-commerce retailers, giving the right search results to users without introducing any technical capabilities or delays is a huge competitive advantage – Adobe</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An improvement in the search functionality of your store will not just improve customer experience but can also affect the conversion rates. Better search results can lead to 1.8x more conversions. Search is the first medium by which the user interacts with your online store.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Utilizing Artificial intelligence and Machine Learning technologies, the merchants get “searchandizing” capabilities that can deliver customized search results for more conversion rates and sales. This feature gives fast search results and is more efficient. In a B2B commerce store especially, it will help retailers enhance the search experience with features like “search-as-you-type”.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The merchants also get accurate reports on the basis of users’ queries and thus they can refine their strategies as per the users’ mindsets and improve sales. The product recommendations will also get improved by these queries which again lead to improved CX and sales. Since it has been powered by Machine Learning, the results will also be more accurate and personalized.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>1. <strong>Live Search Tools</strong>: Adobe Commerce</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":49,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Live-Search-Tools-768x429-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-49\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After installing the Live Search, you will find a screen where you can configure facets, synonyms, rules, or perform API requests in a search engine. Let’s discuss each of these in more detail:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>1. Facets</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You must have found several attributes listed in the filters of a page, mainly a product listing page. These attributes are called <strong>facets</strong>. You can add new attributes in the standard way from Admin -> Attributes -> Product. Here you will find the newly added attributes in the Faceting section of the Live Search Configuration. Again, you have to wait for some time to reflect the newly added attributes populated in the search configuration. The configuration of facets is also very simple. You can configure order and type of sorting and can pin some attributes to have them always on the top of the filter panel.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>2. Synonyms</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many instances when the user types synonyms or related words of a product in the search query. For e.g. the users may type “sneakers” instead of shoes in the query. In the Synonyms tab, you can configure what keywords should be considered synonyms for a particular product name. The best thing here is the ability to set either two-way (search for a dog, leads to pedigree and vice versa) or one way (search for a cloth on head, get scarf but not vice versa).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>3. Rules</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rules are the most exciting feature. Here you can configure how the search results will look based on the searched query. For e.g. you can create a rule that pins a particular product if the search query contains “shoe”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many merchants were waiting for this feature. This is the reality of the e-commerce industry. Search is not just a UX tool that helps users to find a particular product but it also has become a strong marketing tool. Having flexibility over what users will see in your store gives an extra chance to promote your products.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The GraphQL tab is helpful for many developers. It allows to create an API request and see the direct output from the search service.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>2. Under The Hood : Adobe Commerce</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The most appealing fact about the new search is that the search functionality doesn’t take place in the platform itself – earlier it used to be. It collects all the required data about the catalog and sends it to the external search service within Adobe’s infrastructure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The configurations are also stored on this external service as well. If a user searches for a particular keyword, a request will be sent by the system to the mentioned external service using GraphQL. Adobe Sensei will process the service and send back the respective result.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://magento.com/products/live-search\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more about Live Search</a></strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://marketplace.magento.com/magento-live-search.html?_ga=2.14039863.1236502679.1624423008-362010396.1599655295\" target=\"_blank\">Download Live Search for Free</a></strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Wrapping Up</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Searching is an integral part of the ecommerce store UX and it plays a major role in increasing the conversion rates. Adobe Commerce comes with an astonishing search functionality free of cost that other ecommerce platforms are not capable of providing even after using 3rd party paid plugins. Hire the best Adobe Commerce development company, which has expertise in developing Adobe Commerce stores from scratch.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Live Search In Adobe Commerce: How It Improves CX?','In the 2021 Adobe Summit, a new search service called Live Search was introduced for Adobe Commerce. This is an official search solution of Adobe which is focused to bring the searching to a new height by utilizing AI and other advanced technologies.','inherit','closed','closed','','46-revision-v1','','','2023-02-08 21:14:44','2023-02-08 14:14:44','',46,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=50',0,'revision','',0),(51,1,'2023-02-08 21:18:35','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2023-02-08 21:18:35','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=51',0,'post','',0),(52,1,'2023-02-08 21:28:09','2023-02-08 14:28:09','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>AI is the most profound technology we are working on today. Whether it’s helping doctors detect diseases earlier or enabling people to access information in their own language, AI helps people, businesses and communities unlock their potential. And it opens up new opportunities that could significantly improve billions of lives. That’s why we re-oriented the company around AI six years ago — and why we see it as the most important way we can deliver on our mission: to organize the world’s information and make it universally accessible and useful.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since then we’ve continued to make investments in AI across the board, and Google AI and DeepMind are advancing the state of the art. Today, the scale of the largest AI computations is doubling every six months, far outpacing Moore’s Law. At the same time, advanced generative AI and large language models are capturing the imaginations of people around the world. In fact, our Transformer research project and our field-defining paper in 2017, as well as our important advances in diffusion models, are now the basis of many of the generative AI applications you\'re starting to see today.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Introducing Bard</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It’s a really exciting time to be working on these technologies as we translate deep research and breakthroughs into products that truly help people. That’s the journey we’ve been on with large language models. Two years ago we unveiled next-generation language and conversation capabilities powered by our Language Model for Dialogue Applications (or LaMDA for short).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We’ve been working on an experimental conversational AI service, powered by LaMDA, that we’re calling Bard. And today, we’re taking another step forward by opening it up to trusted testers ahead of making it more widely available to the public in the coming weeks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bard seeks to combine the breadth of the world’s knowledge with the power, intelligence and creativity of our large language models. It draws on information from the web to provide fresh, high-quality responses. Bard can be an outlet for creativity, and a launchpad for curiosity, helping you to explain new discoveries from NASA’s James Webb Space Telescope to a 9-year-old, or learn more about the best strikers in football right now, and then get drills to build your skills.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:video -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/original_videos/Super_G_BRD2023_blogEXP_v024a.mp4\"></video><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>Use Bard to simplify complex topics, like explaining new discoveries from NASA’s James Webb Space Telescope to a 9-year-old.</em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:video -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We’re releasing it initially with our lightweight model version of LaMDA. This much smaller model requires significantly less computing power, enabling us to scale to more users, allowing for more feedback. We’ll combine external feedback with our own internal testing to make sure Bard’s responses meet a high bar for quality, safety and groundedness in real-world information. We’re excited for this phase of testing to help us continue to learn and improve Bard’s quality and speed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Bringing the benefits of AI into our everyday products</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We have a long history of using AI to improve Search for billions of people. BERT, one of our first Transformer models, was revolutionary in understanding the intricacies of human language. Two years ago, we introduced MUM, which is 1,000 times more powerful than BERT and has next-level and multi-lingual understanding of information which can pick out key moments in videos and provide critical information, including crisis support, in more languages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now, our newest AI technologies — like LaMDA, PaLM, Imagen and MusicLM — are building on this, creating entirely new ways to engage with information, from language and images to video and audio. We’re working to bring these latest AI advancements into our products, starting with Search.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the most exciting opportunities is how AI can deepen our understanding of information and turn it into useful knowledge more efficiently — making it easier for people to get to the heart of what they’re looking for and get things done. When people think of Google, they often think of turning to us for quick factual answers, like “how many keys does a piano have?” But increasingly, people are turning to Google for deeper insights and understanding — like, “is the piano or guitar easier to learn, and how much practice does each need?” Learning about a topic like this can take a lot of effort to figure out what you really need to know, and people often want to explore a diverse range of opinions or perspectives.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>AI can be helpful in these moments, synthesizing insights for questions where there’s no one right answer. Soon, you’ll see AI-powered features in Search that distill complex information and multiple perspectives into easy-to-digest formats, so you can quickly understand the big picture and learn more from the web: whether that’s seeking out additional perspectives, like blogs from people who play both piano and guitar, or going deeper on a related topic, like steps to get started as a beginner. These new AI features will begin rolling out on Google Search soon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":54,\"width\":840,\"height\":840,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Frame_13213203313x.width-1000.format-webp.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-54\" width=\"840\" height=\"840\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">When looking for insights, AI features in Search can distill information to help you see the big picture.</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Helping developers innovate with AI</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Beyond our own products, we think it’s important to make it easy, safe and scalable for others to benefit from these advances by building on top of our best models. Next month, we’ll start onboarding individual developers, creators and enterprises so they can try our Generative Language API, initially powered by LaMDA with a range of models to follow. Over time, we intend to create a suite of tools and APIs that will make it easy for others to build more innovative applications with AI. Having the necessary compute power to build reliable and trustworthy AI systems is also crucial to startups, and we are excited to help scale these efforts through our Google Cloud partnerships with Cohere, C3.ai and Anthropic, which was just announced last week. Stay tuned for more developer details soon.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Bold and responsible</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It’s critical that we bring experiences rooted in these models to the world in a bold and responsible way. That’s why we’re committed to developing AI responsibly: In 2018, Google was one of the first companies to publish a set of AI Principles. We continue to provide education and resources for our researchers, partner with governments and external organizations to develop standards and best practices, and work with communities and experts to make AI safe and useful.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whether it’s applying AI to radically transform our own products or making these powerful tools available to others, we’ll continue to be bold with innovation and responsible in our approach. And it’s just the beginning — more to come in all of these areas in the weeks and months ahead</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','An important next step on our AI journey','AI is the most profound technology we are working on today. Whether it’s helping doctors detect diseases earlier or enabling people to access information in their own language, AI helps people, businesses and communities unlock their potential.','publish','open','open','','an-important-next-step-on-our-ai-journey','','','2023-02-08 21:30:59','2023-02-08 14:30:59','',0,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=52',0,'post','',0),(53,1,'2023-02-08 21:20:49','2023-02-08 14:20:49','','feb_6_AI_hero.width-1000.format-webp','','inherit','open','closed','','feb_6_ai_hero-width-1000-format-webp','','','2023-02-08 21:20:49','2023-02-08 14:20:49','',52,'https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/feb_6_AI_hero.width-1000.format-webp.webp',0,'attachment','image/webp',0),(54,1,'2023-02-08 21:25:16','2023-02-08 14:25:16','','Frame_13213203313x.width-1000.format-webp','','inherit','open','closed','','frame_13213203313x-width-1000-format-webp','','','2023-02-08 21:25:16','2023-02-08 14:25:16','',52,'https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Frame_13213203313x.width-1000.format-webp.webp',0,'attachment','image/webp',0),(55,1,'2023-02-08 21:28:09','2023-02-08 14:28:09','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>AI is the most profound technology we are working on today. Whether it’s helping doctors detect diseases earlier or enabling people to access information in their own language, AI helps people, businesses and communities unlock their potential. And it opens up new opportunities that could significantly improve billions of lives. That’s why we re-oriented the company around AI six years ago — and why we see it as the most important way we can deliver on our mission: to organize the world’s information and make it universally accessible and useful.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since then we’ve continued to make investments in AI across the board, and Google AI and DeepMind are advancing the state of the art. Today, the scale of the largest AI computations is doubling every six months, far outpacing Moore’s Law. At the same time, advanced generative AI and large language models are capturing the imaginations of people around