oduct recommendations tool takes into account the habits of the buyer as a whole and provides displaying banners, offers related items, upsells, and cross-sells that contribute to average cheque growth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is a win-win solution for both parties. You, as a seller, get more clicks on products and get more orders. And the buyer no longer needs to spend additional time searching for a suitable product.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Automatic Related Products extension can be used to implement such a feature with an extended functions list. You can do it in 2 ways: by implementing the Recommended Products block or by offering bundles.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you want to see the algorithm of creating product recommendation rule, check out the video guide:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/qoCrQ6EIBsg\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/qoCrQ6EIBsg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>What is the Magento recommendation engine?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magento product recommendation engine is a tool that automatically recommends a list of relevant products to the user to encourage them to buy more. Product recommendation engines allow in-store shoppers to receive a set of related products in addition to the products they were interested in.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>What’s the difference between the Magento Recommended Products extension and AI-based platforms for products recommendation?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Simply put, they cover the same marketing task — upselling and cross-selling products to increase average order conversion. Surely, in some way, we can say that AI-based solutions are more data-centered, and therefore, more precise in the choice of products. However, the platforms need to be integrated with your Magento, educated, and, which is more important, all this takes much more money and human resources than installing a ready-made extension for Magento. Magento Recommended Products covers the same business needs and automates the process to save you time and money.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','What is a Magento product recommendation engine and how does it work?','Magento product recommendation engine is a tool that automatically recommends relevant products to a user to encourage buying.','inherit','closed','closed','','57-revision-v1','','','2023-02-09 20:43:38','2023-02-09 13:43:38','',57,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=61',0,'revision','',0),(62,1,'2023-02-09 20:45:02','2023-02-09 13:45:02','','Product Recommendations','','inherit','open','closed','','prec_4','','','2023-02-09 20:46:49','2023-02-09 13:46:49','',0,'https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Prec_4.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(63,1,'2023-02-09 21:02:40','2023-02-09 14:02:40','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Page Builder in Magento that helps in creating content using pre-built drag-and-drop controls. These controls are also defined as “Content Types. The page builder in Magento 2 helps in managing the content effortlessly. Also, it makes it incredibly easy to create content-rich pages with custom layouts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The popularity of drag-and-drop content management tools is in demand for a few years now because non-technical users can operate easily and quickly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":65,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/image-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-65\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using <a href=\"https://devdocs.magento.com/page-builder/docs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Magento 2 page builder</a> you can customize images, text, layout, or placement of the content elements on your webpage by dragging pre-designed rows, columns, blocks, buttons, sliders, etc, and edit them as per your desire.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magento drag and drop page builder provides a fast and intuitive interface for creating category and product content as well as full content pages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Earlier, page builder was only available for the Adobe Commerce version. However, with the release of the Magento 2.4.3 version, <a href=\"https://magento.com/blog/magento-news/bringing-page-builder-content-authoring-magento-open-source-community\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">page builder is available as a bundled extension for open source</a> too!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Therefore, to leverage the full potential of the Magento page builder even if you are an open-source user, upgrade to the latest Magento 2.4.4 version.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Read how Magento 2.4 page builder is going to make the life of store admin much easier with functionalities like drag and drop, live previews, form editors, and more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Top 7 Features of Magento Page Builder:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Drag and Drop availability</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Endless content capabilities</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enriched grid system</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Static and Dynamic blocks</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Creative Visual Effects</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Unlimited Integrations</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enhanced Scheduling facility</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Features of the Magento 2 Page Builder:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>1. Drag and Drop availability</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using page builder for Magento 2, the store owner can easily drag and drop different “Content Types” directly from the sidebar menu of the editing space. This feature effortlessly simplifies how store owners can customize the look and content of your eCommerce website. There is no need to ask for any help from the developers to create a home page, catalog content, product pages, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>2. Endless Content Capabilities</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Featuring rich and quality content is mandatory, and Magento 2.3 page builder empowers the users to build and manage dynamic as well as static content. The drag-and-drop feature possesses endless possibilities for customized design. Live preview functionality helps to review the content on the front end of your store. The store admin is capable of uploading all types of media such as images, videos, and sliders to maps for enhancing the visual experience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All the layouts such as rows, columns, and grids help in writing the content for presenting in the most convenient and pleasing way. Content can be further optimized by designing borders, custom fonts, and text styling options. There are many other components available such as buttons, promotional banners, forms, etc in the Magento landing page builder.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>3. Enriched Grid System</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The grid system is one of the enriched features provided by the Magento 2 CMS page builder. It enables the store admin to add columns of the same or different widths and add different content such as text, images, etc into them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Store admin can effortlessly divide any website into different components and segments to display various content on it. Admin is capable of adding catalog product links so if any customer clicks on that particular grid then the customer will be redirected to that particular product page.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>4. <strong>Static and Dynamic Blocks</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Static blocks recognized as CMS blocks are specific blocks in which information doesn’t change. For example, add a Google Maps static block of your store location or business location because your business location doesn’t change very often.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dynamic blocks are used to display specific segments to your customers. It mainly includes promotional content which is only for a specific section.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>5. Creative Visual Effects</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Basically designing an eCommerce website is all about enabling the capability to customize your images, text, or other content. The page builder in Magento 2 allows a wide scope to fine-tune your content on the webpage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Contains types of borders that can be added to columns and rows. Add customized border color or add different textures such as dotted borders, dashed borders, double borders, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One can add padding to your rows and columns to offer a 3D appearance. You can also enable the parallax background for images. It means you can set the scroll speed of the background a bit slower than your page to induce an immersion effect.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can also include maps and add your customer’s location to it. You can also design your map according to your website theme.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>6. <strong>Unlimited Integrations</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magento 2 page builder allows integrating your favorite third party’s namely Maps, Vimeo, Youtube videos, etc into your web pages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Effortlessly add product lists to any pages on your website. Whether it is the home page, blog pages, landing page, etc. Previously developers had to write complicated codes to import products or product lists on certain pages of your website. But now we can add product lists to our website in just some clicks using the Magento website builder</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>7. Enhanced Scheduling Facility.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Create a page now and go live in the future on another date. Yes, you read it right. You can do that using Magento 2 Page Builder. This feature is the center of attention. Having a super special on this black Friday? You can entirely redesign your store to provide a Black Friday Sale feel and schedule it to go live on that specific date.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>8. <strong>Conclusion</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many eCommerce platforms providing simple user interfaces but store owners have to pay for add-on features that have customization restrictions. Therefore, Magento 2 Page Builder offers better scope for customization and user-friendliness. Store owners can tailor their website and can give a personal touch using Magento 2 Page Builder.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At last, your website will be the face of your business and create the first impression on your customers. Nothing is better than styling your website design and fashioning your website</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Magento 2 Page Builder – Everything you Need to Know [2023]','Page Builder in Magento that helps in creating content using pre-built drag-and-drop controls. These controls are also defined as “Content Types. The page builder in Magento 2 helps in managing the content effortlessly. ','publish','open','open','','magento-2-page-builder-everything-you-need-to-know-2023','','','2023-02-09 21:02:40','2023-02-09 14:02:40','',0,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=63',0,'post','',0),(64,1,'2023-02-09 20:52:53','2023-02-09 13:52:53','','image-2','','inherit','open','closed','','image-2','','','2023-02-09 20:52:53','2023-02-09 13:52:53','',63,'https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/image-2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(65,1,'2023-02-09 21:02:14','2023-02-09 14:02:14','','image-3','','inherit','open','closed','','image-3','','','2023-02-09 21:02:14','2023-02-09 14:02:14','',63,'https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/image-3.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(66,1,'2023-02-09 21:02:40','2023-02-09 14:02:40','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Page Builder in Magento that helps in creating content using pre-built drag-and-drop controls. These controls are also defined as “Content Types. The page builder in Magento 2 helps in managing the content effortlessly. Also, it makes it incredibly easy to create content-rich pages with custom layouts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The popularity of drag-and-drop content management tools is in demand for a few years now because non-technical users can operate easily and quickly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":65,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/image-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-65\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using <a href=\"https://devdocs.magento.com/page-builder/docs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Magento 2 page builder</a> you can customize images, text, layout, or placement of the content elements on your webpage by dragging pre-designed rows, columns, blocks, buttons, sliders, etc, and edit them as per your desire.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magento drag and drop page builder provides a fast and intuitive interface for creating category and product content as well as full content pages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Earlier, page builder was only available for the Adobe Commerce version. However, with the release of the Magento 2.4.3 version, <a href=\"https://magento.com/blog/magento-news/bringing-page-builder-content-authoring-magento-open-source-community\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">page builder is available as a bundled extension for open source</a> too!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Therefore, to leverage the full potential of the Magento page builder even if you are an open-source user, upgrade to the latest Magento 2.4.4 version.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Read how Magento 2.4 page builder is going to make the life of store admin much easier with functionalities like drag and drop, live previews, form editors, and more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Top 7 Features of Magento Page Builder:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Drag and Drop availability</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Endless content capabilities</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enriched grid system</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Static and Dynamic blocks</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Creative Visual Effects</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Unlimited Integrations</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enhanced Scheduling facility</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Features of the Magento 2 Page Builder:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>1. Drag and Drop availability</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using page builder for Magento 2, the store owner can easily drag and drop different “Content Types” directly from the sidebar menu of the editing space. This feature effortlessly simplifies how store owners can customize the look and content of your eCommerce website. There is no need to ask for any help from the developers to create a home page, catalog content, product pages, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>2. Endless Content Capabilities</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Featuring rich and quality content is mandatory, and Magento 2.3 page builder empowers the users to build and manage dynamic as well as static content. The drag-and-drop feature possesses endless possibilities for customized design. Live preview functionality helps to review the content on the front end of your store. The store admin is capable of uploading all types of media such as images, videos, and sliders to maps for enhancing the visual experience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All the layouts such as rows, columns, and grids help in writing the content for presenting in the most convenient and pleasing way. Content can be further optimized by designing borders, custom fonts, and text styling options. There are many other components available such as buttons, promotional banners, forms, etc in the Magento landing page builder.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>3. Enriched Grid System</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The grid system is one of the enriched features provided by the Magento 2 CMS page builder. It enables the store admin to add columns of the same or different widths and add different content such as text, images, etc into them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Store admin can effortlessly divide any website into different components and segments to display various content on it. Admin is capable of adding catalog product links so if any customer clicks on that particular grid then the customer will be redirected to that particular product page.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>4. <strong>Static and Dynamic Blocks</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Static blocks recognized as CMS blocks are specific blocks in which information doesn’t change. For example, add a Google Maps static block of your store location or business location because your business location doesn’t change very often.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dynamic blocks are used to display specific segments to your customers. It mainly includes promotional content which is only for a specific section.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>5. Creative Visual Effects</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Basically designing an eCommerce website is all about enabling the capability to customize your images, text, or other content. The page builder in Magento 2 allows a wide scope to fine-tune your content on the webpage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Contains types of borders that can be added to columns and rows. Add customized border color or add different textures such as dotted borders, dashed borders, double borders, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One can add padding to your rows and columns to offer a 3D appearance. You can also enable the parallax background for images. It means you can set the scroll speed of the background a bit slower than your page to induce an immersion effect.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can also include maps and add your customer’s location to it. You can also design your map according to your website theme.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>6. <strong>Unlimited Integrations</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magento 2 page builder allows integrating your favorite third party’s namely Maps, Vimeo, Youtube videos, etc into your web pages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Effortlessly add product lists to any pages on your website. Whether it is the home page, blog pages, landing page, etc. Previously developers had to write complicated codes to import products or product lists on certain pages of your website. But now we can add product lists to our website in just some clicks using the Magento website builder</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>7. Enhanced Scheduling Facility.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Create a page now and go live in the future on another date. Yes, you read it right. You can do that using Magento 2 Page Builder. This feature is the center of attention. Having a super special on this black Friday? You can entirely redesign your store to provide a Black Friday Sale feel and schedule it to go live on that specific date.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>8. <strong>Conclusion</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many eCommerce platforms providing simple user interfaces but store owners have to pay for add-on features that have customization restrictions. Therefore, Magento 2 Page Builder offers better scope for customization and user-friendliness. Store owners can tailor their website and can give a personal touch using Magento 2 Page Builder.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At last, your website will be the face of your business and create the first impression on your customers. Nothing is better than styling your website design and fashioning your website</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Magento 2 Page Builder – Everything you Need to Know [2023]','Page Builder in Magento that helps in creating content using pre-built drag-and-drop controls. These controls are also defined as “Content Types. The page builder in Magento 2 helps in managing the content effortlessly. ','inherit','closed','closed','','63-revision-v1','','','2023-02-09 21:02:40','2023-02-09 14:02:40','',63,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=66',0,'revision','',0),(67,1,'2023-02-09 21:17:23','2023-02-09 14:17:23','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magento 2 Multi-Source Inventory was introduced in the Magento 2.3.3 version release.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The concept of salable quantity came into existence with the Magento 2 MSI and this post explains the <strong><em>difference between Magento 2 salable quantity and quantity</em></strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have downloaded the Magento 2.3.3 version and checked, you’ll see the product grid displays the salable quantity and quantity:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":68,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/image-4-1024x357.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-68\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let’s understand these two terms and their difference in Magento 2.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>1. Difference Between Magento 2 Salable Quantity and Quantity:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Salable Quantity is the sum of available resources, grouped in stocks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unlike in previous versions of Magento 2, the quantity of a product does not decrease when the customer places an order. Instead, the salable quantity gets reduced.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While. the quantity of the product decrease only after shipping is completed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The salable quantity is updated when:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The physical quantity in the warehouse changes</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A new order is placed by the customer</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magento 2 MSI removes the limitation of relying on a single inventory system only. Now, the merchants can manage their inventory in more than one locations to accurately reflect their physical inventories without any 3rd party extensions!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The salable quantity is stored in view.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>2. Understanding the workflow of order placement &amp; changes in Magento salable quantity and quantity:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/tjsmy9QALsg\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed aligncenter is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/tjsmy9QALsg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When a customer places an order, the salable quantity is reduced. Note that, the quantity is not decreased even when the order is placed.<br>Now when the admin creates the shipment for the order from the backend, we can see that the quantity is reduced as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Any doubts about salable quantity and quantity in Magento 2? If so, please mention them in the Comments section below.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Also, do share the solution with the Magento community via social media.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thank you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Magento 2 Salable Quantity vs Quantity – Know the Difference','The concept of salable quantity came into existence with the Magento 2 MSI and this post explains the difference between Magento 2 salable quantity and quantity.','publish','open','open','','magento-2-salable-quantity-vs-quantity-know-the-difference','','','2023-02-09 21:17:23','2023-02-09 14:17:23','',0,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=67',0,'post','',0),(68,1,'2023-02-09 21:12:24','2023-02-09 14:12:24','','image-4','','inherit','open','closed','','image-4','','','2023-02-09 21:12:24','2023-02-09 14:12:24','',67,'https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/image-4.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(69,1,'2023-02-09 21:16:30','2023-02-09 14:16:30','','image-5','','inherit','open','closed','','image-5','','','2023-02-09 21:16:30','2023-02-09 14:16:30','',67,'https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/image-5.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(70,1,'2023-02-09 21:17:23','2023-02-09 14:17:23','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magento 2 Multi-Source Inventory was introduced in the Magento 2.3.3 version release.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The concept of salable qua