elopment. It’s an exciting concept but one that could pose some interesting challenges if implemented widely. For instance, how would ChatGPT handle complex tasks? How would it integrate with existing systems? Would its output be reliable and secure enough for production use?<br>These are questions that have yet to be answered, but it’s clear that this AI tool has the potential to change the way developers work but not to completely replace them.”</td></tr><tr><td><img class=\"wp-image-76\" style=\"width: 150px;\" src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/image-9.png\" alt=\"\"></td><td><strong>“ChatGPT Lacks Creative Problem-Solving Skills” – Luke Fitzpatrick, CEO at Drsono</strong>.<br><br>“ChatGPT is an AI that automates writing code and has the potential to replace developers. However, there are some drawbacks to this technology that need to be considered. While ChatGPT may be able to process large chunks of code faster than a human, it lacks the creative problem-solving skills that developers bring to the table.<br>Developers often use their expertise to think outside the box and devise innovative new solutions to complex coding issues, something ChatGPT cannot do. The truth is ChatGPT could possibly supplement and complement skilled developers but ultimately cannot replace them entirely.”</td></tr><tr><td><img class=\"wp-image-77\" style=\"width: 150px;\" src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/image-10.png\" alt=\"\"></td><td><strong>“Developers Still Needed for Quality Checking” – William Hogsett, CEO at Seota Digital Marketing.</strong><br><br>“I don’t believe that ChatGPT will replace developers completely. With the rate AI is being developed, it could possibly take over some tasks in the near future, but not all. Firstly, though it will likely be able to generate higher-quality code in the future, it will still need developers to examine and quality-check the data it provides.<br>Additionally, as it’s a language generator, it’s not able to be truly innovative or creative – two very important skills for developers. Finally, even if it someday learns to do everything a developer can, ChatGPT itself will still need developers to maintain and update it.”</td></tr><tr><td><img class=\"wp-image-78\" style=\"width: 150px;\" src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/image-11.png\" alt=\"\"></td><td><strong>“No Tech is Proven to Replace Creativity” – Jake Albion, Owner of Albion Digital Web Studio.</strong><br><br>“No. It will make them more effective, like many other tools used to code, including GitHub Copilot or Emmet, and research solutions faster. You’ll still need to be able to understand how everything works.<br>Developers can focus on complex problems and reduce repetitive tasks, especially on platforms like WordPress. It may also widen the disparity of developers vs non-coders, but that won’t be for a while until it becomes more reliable for people who don’t want to code and hack shortcuts for their websites. Ultimately that means that people who understand how to conceptualize, plan, and develop software and websites (experts) will become more valuable and be able to charge more for their time.<br>The spectrum of how we work is widening, creating more opportunities, not less, mainly because no technology has proven to replace creativity and problem-solving.”</td></tr><tr><td><img class=\"wp-image-79\" style=\"width: 150px;\" src=\"https://sharing.knowledge/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/image-12.png\" alt=\"\"></td><td><strong>“AI Won’t Steal Your Job; Person Using AI Will” – Marcin Gwizdala, Chief Technical Officer at Tidio.</strong><br><br>“ChatGPT or AI in general will not replace developers. The person who uses AI will. In my opinion, this is the only valid response when it comes to the fear of AI stealing one’s job. The tool itself simply cannot do it. However, those developers that take advantage of emerging technologies adapt fast and learn to be proficient users of them have every chance to grow in their career much faster than the rest.<br>The modern tech environment does not tolerate stagnation. One can be sure that if they are not willing to grow, they will be replaced by someone possibly less experienced, but advanced with AI tools. We have to adapt to these conditions, whether we like it or not.”</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Is ChatGPT going to replace programmers?</strong> — Well, <strong>surely not</strong>, according to these seven experts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tools such as ChatGPT can speed up the development process and reduce mundane tasks for developers. This will allow the professionals to spend more time on creative solutions and problem-solving. Professionals can elevate their efficiency and capabilities by synergizing with such tools.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a nutshell, considering the current status, we should think of ChatGPT as a human assistant rather than a replacement. 😇</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Will ChatGPT Replace Developers? – 7 Experts Share Their Views','OpenAI’s ChatGPT is a hot topic amongst internet users these days; the reason is simple: it can do almost anything!  So, will ChatGPT replace programmers?','inherit','closed','closed','','71-revision-v1','','','2023-02-09 21:36:06','2023-02-09 14:36:06','',71,'https://sharing.knowledge/?p=82',0,'revision','',0),(83,1,'2023-02-09 21:37:23','2023-02-09 14:37:23','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Will ChatGPT replace programmers? Here’s what experts think about it. 💡</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://openai.com/blog/chatgpt/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">OpenAI’s ChatGPT</a> is a hot topic amongst internet users these days; the reason is simple:<strong> it can do almost anything! 😉</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It had a r